<TEXT>
michael s dukakis clinched the democratic 
presidential nomination on tuesday night assuring his victory on 
the first ballot at the partys national convention according to 
the associated press delegate count 
the massachusetts governor exceeded the 2081 delegate majority 
as votes were being counted in the california primary earlier 
dukakis picked up more than 100 delegates in winning the three other 
finalday primaries in new jersey new mexico and montana 
dukakis began the day about 150 delegates short and was likely to 
end the evening with about 2200 delegates in the ap count on 
wednesday he expected to pick up more delegates and the 
endorsements of two former rivals 
george bush mathematically clinched the republican nomination in 
winning the pennsylvania primary in april 
