<TEXT>
edward schaumberg quade a founder of 
the methodical problemsolving method known as systems analysis 
died saturday he was 79 
quade joined the research organization when it was founded in 
1948 and retired in 1973 his 1968 book systems analysis and 
policy planning applications in defense defined systems analysis 
as a systematic approach to helping a decisionmaker choose a 
course of action by investigating his full problem searching out 
objectives and alternatives and comparing them in the light of 
their consequences 
quades books applied systems analysis to military problems and 
later to broader public policy issues 
</TEXT>
