<TEXT>
japan is trimming its huge trade surplus by 
expanding imports and stepping up overseas investment the ministry 
of international trade and industry said today 
but the united states must do its part for the world economy by 
easing its budget and trade deficits the ministry said in a report 
summing up japans foreign trade in 1987 
it also said japan should play a bigger role in asian development 
through direct investment and importing more of the regions 
manufactured goods 
the report issued annually since 1949 praises ongoing 
structural changes that have improved access to the japanese market 
for foreign exporters of manufactured goods 
manufactured imports are increasing rapidly and the 
distribution system in japan is undergoing a change said atsushi 
oi head of the ministrys international trade research office 
japans trade surplus fell in fiscal 1987 for the first time in 
six years from 10165 billion in 1986 to 9428 billion according 
to japanese figures 
still japans trade surplus with the united states continued to 
climb hitting 49 billion in december 1987 from 47 billion a 
year earlier the latest government figures show 
oi said increased exports of capital goods to the united states 
contributed to the increase capital goods exports are rising as 
japanese firms send equipment to set up us production facilities 
secondly and this has a bigger share is that american 
companies look to excellent capital goods exports from japan and 
install these in their plants oi said 
finance minister kiichi miyazawa said exports bound for the 
united states will fall from the present 40 percent share of japans 
total to 2530 percent as japan restructures its exportdriven 
economy toward domestic demand 
he did not give a time frame 
the trade ministry report says japanese imports grew by 93 
percent in 1987 over the previous year while export volume rose 
only 03 percent 
oi said the united states can lessen its trade deficit by cutting 
down on excessive consumer demand expanding production facilities 
and revamping its export policy 
the report says the us trade deficit hit 1712 billion in 
1987 up 15 billion over 1986 
us exports to japan rose by a meager 84 percent in 1987 but 
those from asias newly industrialized countries of south korea 
taiwan and hong kong soared by 503 percent the report says 
the white paper is cautious about the future of japans 
restructuring it says that while imports are growing along with 
domestic demand nations awash in surplus funds like japan must 
expand imports and provide a stable supply of capital to debtor 
nations 
the role of japan from now on is to help asian countries create 
a region of development that is open to the rest of the world 
oi said 
