<TEXT>
critical information is disappearing momentarily 
from air traffic controllers screens in airports for dallas 
houston los angeles and atlanta because of a computer glitch a 
newspaper reported today 
information on altitude airspeed aircraft types call signs and 
destinations vanish from radar screens for up to 20 seconds said 
the dallas morning news quoting federal aviation administration 
officials 
faa officials do not believe the error in a computer program 
presents a hazard to safety lawrence parrent assistant air traffic 
manager at dallasfort worth international airport said monday 
the radar has not failed parrent said the primary target 
is still there the radar image and a fourdigit number assigned 
to each aircraft known as a target by controllers remain on 
the screen 
controllers are concerned about the glitch and are monitoring the 
faas progress in fixing it said edward f mullin a local 
representative of the national air traffic controllers association 
its a new program and there are some software problems he 
said i dont think thats anything unusual were not totally 
comfortable with it but theyre working hard on the system 
the information disappears when the program detects a glitch in 
the system parrent said 
when information is about to disappear an alarm sounds and 
controllers have up to five seconds to write down the information or 
memorize it faa officials told the morning news controllers handle 
up to 10 aircraft at a time 
the new program offers many features that improve the margin of 
safety and bugs will be worked out parrent said 
however the newspaper said some aviation experts and controllers 
voiced concern that although horizontal distance between aircraft 
still can be tracked on the screen the glitch could cause problems 
the risk is exacerbated if the problem occurs when aircraft are 
in a holding pattern because of bad weather said len nahmi a 
californiabased airline captain and air safety investigator 
it is common for aircraft to be in holding patterns with altitude 
separations of 1000 feet in weather that severely limits 
visibility nahmi said 
if a pilot deviated from an assigned altitude when information 
disappeared the controller would be unable to detect the change 
and a collision would be likely he said 
parrent acknowleged the glitches have made some controllers 
uneasy 
it does cause tense moments in the control room he said 
but we would not run that program if there was a derogation of 
safety 
</TEXT>
