<TEXT>
a latin american effort to negotiate a 
settlement to the political crisis in panama got off to an 
unpromising start last week when military leader manuel antonio 
noriega showed no inclination to surrender power according a senior 
administration official 
the official insisting on anonymity said noriega showed an 
unwillngness to compromise and no give in his meeting with former 
presidents caros andres perez of venezuela and daniel oduber of 
costa rica 
the meeting was held a week after a us negotiating effort 
collapsed when noriega unexpectedly rejected a package deal at the 
last minute that would have required him to resign his post as 
defense force commander in august and temporarily leave the country 
in an interview monday assistant secretary of state elliott 
