lastminute homestate pressure would cause three senators to relent 
and provide the twothirds margin needed to override reagans veto 
of the 1000page bill designed to strengthen the us position in 
the international marketplace 
centerpiece provisions would overhaul the system under which the 
government imposes import curbs as a means of aiding us industries 
and punishing international trade violations by other countries 
a wide array of other provisions range from hefty agricultural 
subsidies to repeal of the 1980 windfall profits tax on oilindustry 
earnings 
the president vetoed the bill may 24 focusing heavily on 
opposition to a provision that would require companies with 100 
employees or more to provide notice to their workers of impending 
plant closings and largescale layoffs 
in short order the house voted 308113 to override the veto and 
approve the bill but supporters of the measure have found the 
senate tougher going 
were winning senate minority leader bob dole rkan a 
critic of the measure told reporters weve got 36 votes 
even if one senator democrat joseph biden of delaware were not 
at home recuperating from surgery opponents would be able to put an 
override out of reach if they could muster 34 votes in the 
100member senate 
