the trade bill once the senate sustains the veto 
there has been cloakroom talk that some senators looking at their 
reelection campaigns feel more comfortable about supporting the 
veto if they are assured that there will be another chance to vote 
on the trade issue before congress adjourns in october 
but it remains uncertain whether there will be such a second 
bill byrd has repeatedly raised the possibility that a raft of 
potential amendments that already have been taken care of over the 
last three years would reappear and stall the measure amid lengthy 
debate 
there will have to be some agreement between the ledership and 
