was to meet with darios beshir bahr elghazals regional govenor 
tem said relief supplies had not reached aweil since a consignment 
of rice and edible oil arrived by train a year ago 
prime minister sadek elmahdi has not replied to an appeal for 
food and medicine addressed to the government and to western relief 
organizations tem said adding he was trying to meet with elmahdi 
to urge him to declare aweil a hunger area 
elmahdi has announced that the united nations is sponsoring a 
program to transport relief food to the south but no date has been 
set for the operation 
the spla took up arms against the government in 1983 to demand 
more autonomy and administrative and economic reforms the years of 
fighting have corresponded with one of the worst famines in sudan in 
years 
