when governors pack their bags and passports 
where do they go 
in 1987 they headed most often to japan according to a survey 
by the national governors association 
it said governors from 43 states and territories made 87 overseas 
trips during 1987 often stopping in more than one country 
but the most frequent destination was japan 36 trips followed 
by korea 19 taiwan and england both 17 west germany 13 
china and france both 9 canada italy and hong kong all 6 and 
switzerland belgium and the netherlands all 3 
honduras panama and the soviet union were each visited twice 
countries that drew a single governor were anguilla australia 
austria denmark ecuador egypt finland ireland india israel 
luxembourg malaysia mexico new caledonia saipan st lucia 
sweden thailand venezuela and western samoa 
the association said governors usually go abroad to encourage 
us exports increase foreign investment and promote tourism 
the 87 trips was nearly double the 45 overseas trips governors 
made in 1986 
nowadays most governors are making one to five overseas trips 
a year to sell their states resources goods and services 
according to an article in the governors weekly bulletin 
