rep claude pepper marshaled an array of 
influential lawmakers tuesday as he prepared for a doordie effort 
in the house to pass a costly new home health care program 
peppers plan scheduled for floor action wednesday would expand 
medicare to include longterm home care benefits for anyone of any 
age who is chronically ill or cant perform tasks of daily living 
with opponents mobilizing to prevent a vote on the bill pepper 
rallied his own forces tuesday at a news conference sens edward 
kennedy dmass chairman of the senate labor and human resources 
committee sen paul simon dill the senate sponsor of the bill 
and reps richard gephardt dmo who holds the no 4 leadership 
position in the house and henry waxman dcalif chairman of the 
house energy and commerce health subcommittee 
we have a total vacuum when it comes to longterm care 
pepper dfla said a million people a year become destitute 
trying to pay for catastrophic care 
the pepper bill has provoked criticism on several counts among 
them its high cost its lack of a nursing home component and the 
unorthodox manner in which it bypassed committee scrutiny and sped 
to the house floor 
we should not allow the rules of the house to be manipulated to 
satisfy the popular issue of the moment house ways and means 
committee chairman dan rostenkowski dill said tuesday in a 
letter to his colleagues he said the committee system protects 
members from being forced to vote on popularappearing proposals 
that may ultimately prove to be embarrassing 
the pepper bill is putting house members particularly democrats 
in a bind because withiout their support there is no chance congress 
will pass the bill before adjourning this year 
there is overwhelming public sentiment in favor of a longterm 
care program there also is an election in six months and the 
87yearold pepper who is popular with elderly voters has made 
campaign appearances on behalf of many lawmakers in the past 
the congressional budget office estimates the home care program 
would cost nearly 28 billion over five years it would be paid for 
by imposing the medicare payroll tax on income above 45000 which 
is currently exempt 
supporters of the plan also backed a new catastrophic care 
benefit bill to help the elderly cope with acute illness that 
medicare expansion more than a year in the making has passed the 
house and is expected to pass the senate this week 
but waxman called that measure only half the roof that people 
need to shield them from health care catastrophes i always feel 
guilty calling this other bill the catastrophic bill 
pepper initially tried to attach his plan to the catastrophic 
bill but withdrew it when lawmakers said it would sink that 
legislation in return house speaker jim wright dtexas agreed to 
let pepper have a separate floor vote on his plan 
pepper chairman of the rules committee that schedules floor 
action scheduled his own bill last year effectively bypassing 
rostenkowskis committee and the energy and commerce committee 
