would face an annual deficit within five years 
pepper dismissed the notion that he was abusing the committee 
process saying what happened with his bill was unique and would not 
become routine 
the rules committee is not going to run rampant over anybody 
pepper said tuesday all they want to do is kill the bill and use 
the money for something else 
in a dear colleague letter of their own dated june 8 pepper 
and his cosponsor rep edward roybal dcalif called cost and 
procedure issues bogus reasons to oppose the bill 
they said the bill contains a cap on costs and does not violate 
any procedural rules of the house 
they also said outside opposition groups such as the insurance 
industry would oppose any longterm care bill because they serve 
their own narrow selfinterest not the american peoples interest 
