in durban however the federated chamber of industries said the 
strike had intensified around the nations thirdlargest city 
black labor unions and antiapartheid groups called the threeday 
protest which the government says is illegal to oppose the 
2yearold state of emergency and proposed legislation to restrict 
the rights of unions to strike 
the congress of south african trade unions the largest black 
