<TEXT>
the suicide rate among jail inmates is 
nine times greater than that of the general population and continues 
to be the leading cause of death in city and county lockups 
according to a federally financed study released tuesday 
although the average length of stay in jail is approximately 6 
to 11 days 51 percent of all jail suicide victims were dead within 
the first 24 hours of incarceration and 29 percent committed suicide 
within the first three hours the national center on institutions 
and alternatives said 
while alcoholdrug related and minor other charges account 
for 37 percent of offenses for which jail inmates are confined they 
represented 55 percent of all suicide victims according to the 
study of jail suicides in 198586 
lindsay m hayes directed the project which was supported 
through a grant from the national institute of corrections in the 
department of justice hayes said the suicide rate in detention 
facilities was found to be 107 per 100000 inmates census bureau 
studies show he said that the rate is 125 per 100000 in the 
general population 
further suicide continues to be the leading cause of death in 
our nations jails hayes said in a statement 
texas california new york and illinois recorded 32 percent of 
all the suicides in the study those states according to justice 
department figures also house one in three jail inmates 
the numbers of suicides in jails was 453 in 1985 and 401 in 1986 
the study said 
the findings also showed that 72 percent of the suicide victims 
were white 94 percent were male the average age of the victim was 
30 60 percent of the victims were intoxicated at the time they were 
jailed and two of three victims were in isolation 
while black inmates comprise 41 percent of the jail population 
they acounted for only 16 percent of the jail suicides the study 
said while 31 percent of jail inmates are intoxicated by alcohol 
upon arrest over 60 percent of jail suicide victims were 
intoxicated upon arrest 
only rhode island and vermont recorded no jail suicides in the 
twoyear period 
