troops will be implemented and the other parties will not live up 
to their commitments najib said 
about 55 million people roughly onethird of the population 
have fled afghanistan in 10 years of civil war more than 3 million 
to pakistan and 2 million to iran 
the unmediated agreement signed april 14 in geneva requires 
the soviets to withdraw the more than 100000 red army soldiers who 
have been helping fight moslem rebels in afghanistan 
soviet officials also have threatened to slow the withdrawal 
in a statement may 28 announcing that 10000 soldiers had left 
afghanistan the soviet foreign ministry said the pullout could slow 
if the united states kept delivering lavish supplies to the 
rebels 
najib spoke to the general assembly disarmament session for 30 
minutes devoting most of his remarks to the situation in 
afghanistan he again called for national reconciliation and 
establishment of a coalition government including opposition forces 
he said the death toll in the war was 243900 soldiers and 
civilians including 35700 women and 20700 children he said 
77700 people have been wounded 
moslem guerrillas began fighting in afghanistan after a communist 
coup in april 1978 and soviet military forces entered the country in 
december 1979 
the insurgents were not involved in the geneva negotiations 
leaders of the sevenparty guerrilla coalition have said they would 
ignore the agreement and continue fighting 
