<TEXT>
a rural north dakota factory is making it 
easier to locate baggage at busy airports place bets at las vegas 
casinos and even find love in a bustling east coast singles bar 
northstar enterprises inc makes computerized indoor message 
boards and signs and is winning acceptance as one of the leaders in 
the industry 
we really feel were the cadillac of the business said 
northstar president allan larson thats what were shooting for 
larson declines to disclose the 9yearold companys sales 
figures but said they have grown by 20 percent to 30 percent a year 
since it was founded 
he predicts that the lightemitting diode industry in five years 
should reach 200 million in sales and he believes northstar will 
capture up to 20 percent of the market 
the opportunities are just unlimited said larson 
the industry is relatively new about six us companies are 
manufacturing electronic message systems and most are less than a 
decade old 
northstar started in 1979 with five products it now offers more 
than 30 and is doing more custom design work said larson who 
joined the company in 1980 and became president in 1982 
northstars message boards can be programmed for hundreds of 
different messages from a computer keyboard the messages can be 
programmed to run laterally or up and down and can be accompanied by 
graphics or animation 
the message boards can be custombuilt to any specifications but 
many of the signs come with letters about 7 inches to 8 inches high 
larson said the boards are generally long but only about as deep as 
the letters 
the signs are made up of hundreds of bulbs most come with red 
bulbs which light up according to a computer command to form 
messages 
specialized software is where the future lies said dewey 
olson vice president and national sales manager and the last of 
northstars three founders still with the company 
northstar was founded by two mayville men olson and dale beck 
and a chicagobased computer consultant steve hogan who saw an 
untapped market for electronic message systems 
the company operates out of a 5000squarefoot plant located 
between mayville population 2255 and portland population 627 
about 55 miles north of fargo nd the plant employs 22 people 
fulltime and another dozen parttimers are on the payroll 
in 1986 northstar merged with lexicon inc a salt lake 
citybased company that made computer software 
the company has placed boards in airports casinos hospitals 
restaurants bars bowling alleys financial institutions and 
schools nationwide 
northstar boards flash instant odds on sporting events at 
caesars palace in las vegas and harrahs in atlantic city nj 
several midsize airports use the boards to help travelers locate 
baggage and boarding areas the company also has completed a deal 
with the baltimore mass transit system olson said 
in addition northstar has developed what it believes to be the 
first electronic display cardiac alert system in the nation larson 
said the system which has been in use at the bethesda naval 
hospital for four years allows medical personnel to alert 27 
critical areas of the hospital simultaneously during an emergency 
involving a heart patient he says 
looking to the future company officials see its message boards 
used as promotional devices on city buses subway cars and 
paytelephones company officials believe the airport industry 
provides the greatest potential and olson said he is already 
working on more projects with major airports around the country 
one of the most unusual uses of the companys message boards has 
been in a game called selectrocution played in east coast singles 
bars in the game bar patrons use a message board to make 
acquaintances the game ends with the patrons being ranked for 
desirability by others in the bar and matched by computer at 
evenings end with anyone expressing mutual interest 
with bids out on more than 16 million worth of projects and 
several others already in the works larson feels the future holds 
promise for his company 
our products are applicable in so many areas its hard to 
narrow the scope to areas that will have the greatest impact 
larson said were trying to look at key markets where we can 
concentrate and do a good job 
