percent in 1987 over the previous year the trade ministry said 
those from the newly industrialized countries of south korea 
taiwan hong kong and singapore soared by 503 percent in the same 
period according to the trade report 
by comparison imports of us consumer goods rose only 84 
percent 
since early 1985 the yen has risen by more than 100 percent 
against the us dollar making japanese exports more expensive 
overseas but boosting japans import buying power 
oi said japan is prepared to import more manufactured goods from 
asian nations and step up direct investment in the region 
he said asias newly industrialized countries have depended on 
the us market for their development but it will be difficult to 
continue to depend on exports to the united states 
to offset the burden on us markets japan was prepared to help 
by absorbing more asian products and offering technological and 
economic assistance as well as stepping up direct investment he 
said 
