<TEXT>
the government said tuesday that it would offer the 
stateowned bank girobank for sale to a financial institution 
girobank formally national giro is britains sixthlargest 
bank it was set up in 1968 to cater to the banking needs of 
workingclass britons and is now part of the post office 
industry minister kenneth clarke announced the governments 
latest privatization in the house of commons saying the bank now 
needs to expand vigorously 
the sale of the bank which analysts said could raise 300 million 
pounds or about 543 million is expected to take place by the end 
of the year 
merchant bankers will be in charge of assessing the bids for 
girobank under the guidance of the post office 
the bank which has about 25 million customers had pretax 
profit last year of 231 million british pounds or about 42 
million on revenue of 328 million pounds or 594 million 
it will be important to safeguard close links between 
girobank and post office counters clarke said 
conservative prime minister margaret thatcher has previously 
ruled out the privatization of the nations mail delivery service 
but not of other postal operations 
in addition to the bank and the royal mail the post office also 
oversees a subsidiary which runs the counters where stamps are sold 
parcels weighed and banking services provided 
opposition lawmaker tony benn who as labor government postmaster 
general launched girobank 22 years ago said the privatization of 
the bank was a naked act of plunder of a public asset which had 
been wildly successful 
although the offer price will be a major factor in deciding who 
takes over the bank it will not simply be sold to the highest 
bidder clarke said 
the government will also look at the bidders plans for 
developing the bank the impact of the sale on the post office and 
other factors he said 
clarke signaled government opposition to a takeover of girobank 
by any of the big four commercial banking companies national 
westminster bank plc barclays bank plc midland bank plc and lloyds 
bank plc 
girobank is primarily used as a savings bank by retired and poor 
people who dont need all the services of a retail bank 
girobank issues checks and has post office hours which are 
longer than bank hours it is also used to pay gas electricity and 
other bills as well as to wire money within britain and abroad 
girobank has reached a new fiveyear contract with the counters 
subsidiary through which it operates clarke said 
mrs thatcher has sold off billions of pounds worth of 
stateowned assets primarily through the sale of shares to the 
public as a way of promoting capitalism in britain 
companies sold off include british telecommunications plc the 
phone company which also used to be run by the post office 
